## Fastpath SUT Login & Permissions Test

From the local workstation, run the following against the SUT (replace <SUT_IP>):

1. SSH connectivity: `ssh fpuser@<SUT_IP> 'whoami && hostname'`
2. Group membership: `ssh fpuser@<SUT_IP> 'id'` (must include `sudo` and `docker`).
3. Passwordless sudo: `ssh fpuser@<SUT_IP> 'sudo -n true'`.
4. Docker access: `ssh fpuser@<SUT_IP> 'docker ps'`.
5. SSH config perms: `ssh fpuser@<SUT_IP> 'ls -ld ~/.ssh && ls -l ~/.ssh'` (700 dir, 600 files).
6. Sudoers entry: `ssh ubuntu@<SUT_IP> 'sudo cat /etc/sudoers.d/fpuser'`.

All commands must succeed without password prompts.
